# frontend/.env.example
# Copy to .env for local development.
# Vite only exposes variables prefixed with VITE_ to the browser bundle.
# Never put secrets here. These values are baked into the compiled JS.

# ── API base URL ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# In development: points to Nginx proxy on localhost
# In production: your Coolify domain
VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost/api

# ── Environment ────────────────────────────────────────────────
VITE_APP_ENV=development
```

---

## Checklist Before Running the Test Commands

Before running `docker compose build`, verify:
```
finscopemx/
├── docker-compose.yml          (exists, all 6 services defined)
├── docker-compose.dev.yml      (exists)
├── nginx/
│   └── nginx.conf              (exists)
├── backend/
│   ├── Dockerfile              (exists)
│   ├── .dockerignore           (exists)
│   ├── .env.example            (exists)
│   ├── requirements.txt        (must exist, even if empty for now)
│   ├── alembic.ini             (can be a stub for now)
│   └── app/
│       └── main.py             (must exist with a minimal FastAPI app)
└── frontend/
    ├── Dockerfile              (exists)
    ├── .dockerignore           (exists)
    ├── nginx-spa.conf          (exists)
    ├── .env.example            (exists)
    └── package.json            (must exist)
